Subject: [PATCH] btrfs: Return EXDEV for cross file system snapshot

EXDEV seems an appropriate error if an operation fails bacause it
crosses file system boundaries.

Reviewed-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.cz>
Signed-off-by: Kusanagi Kouichi <slash@ac.auone-net.jp>
Signed-off-by: Josef Bacik <jbacik@fb.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.cz>
---
 fs/btrfs/ioctl.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/btrfs/ioctl.c
+++ b/fs/btrfs/ioctl.c
@@ -1537,7 +1537,7 @@ static noinline int btrfs_ioctl_snap_cre
 		if (src_inode->i_sb != file_inode(file)->i_sb) {
 			printk(KERN_INFO "btrfs: Snapshot src from "
 			       "another FS\n");
-			ret = -EINVAL;
+			ret = -EXDEV;
 			fput(src_file);
 			goto out_drop_write;
 		} else if (!inode_owner_or_capable(src_inode)) {
